105707.name: Age-standardised raised blood pressure prevalence (male)
105707.description:
Share of adult men (aged 18+ years) with raised blood pressure. This data is age-standardized, which means the age structure of the population is assumed to be constant to allow for comparison between countries and over time.

Raised blood pressure (BP) is defined as systolic BP 140 mmHg, or diastolic BP 90 mmHg.

display.name: Share of men with high blood pressure

105707.datasetName: Raised Blood Pressure Prevalence - NCD RisC (2017)

source.name: NCD RisC (2017)
source.dataPublishedBy: Zhou, B., Bentham, J., Di Cesare, M., Bixby, H., Danaei, G., Cowan, M. J., ... & Taddei, C. (2017). Worldwide trends in blood pressure from 1975 to 2015: a pooled analysis of 1479 population-based measurement studies with 19.1 million participants. The Lancet, 389(10064), 37-55.
source.additionalInfo:
This dataset presents crude and age-standardised estimates of the prevalence of raised blood pressure by country, region, and globally for men and women.

Raised blood pressure (BP) is defined as systolic BP 140 mmHg, or diastolic BP 90 mmHg.

The data was pooled from 1,479 studies that had measured the blood pressures of 19.1 million adults.
